  "privileged_info_summary": "The solar_suitability_analysis task uses a synthetic DEM (500\u00d7500 pixels, 10m resolution, EPSG:32610) generated by a Gaussian hill formula. The task evaluates land suitability for solar farms using two criteria: slope < 10\u00b0 and aspect 135-225\u00b0 (south-facing in Northern Hemisphere, using GDAL's azimuth convention: 0\u00b0=N, 90\u00b0=E, 180\u00b0=S, 270\u00b0=W). The synthetic DEM ranges from ~50m to ~301m elevation with a tilted plane component to ensure south-facing slopes exist. Ground truth is computed using GDAL's DEMProcessing functions. The verifier applies tolerances (slope \u00b12\u00b0, aspect \u00b15\u00b0) to account for algorithm variations. Input path: /home/ga/GIS_Data/elevation.tif; output path: /home/ga/GIS_Data/exports/solar_candidates.tif.",
